<v Rian>Okay, this makes sense.
So everything is announced,

00:42:18.650 --> 00:42:21.694
but it's not really attached
to anything in the form,

00:42:21.719 --> 00:42:26.215
so if someone changes things,
and goes over the form,

00:42:26.240 --> 00:42:28.236
the information is not repeated.

00:42:28.260 --> 00:42:30.654
Only on when the change happens.

00:42:31.217 --> 00:42:33.674
Now we saw several ways to solve this.

00:42:33.698 --> 00:42:37.797
You can add an
aria-describedby to the amount,

00:42:37.822 --> 00:42:39.544
pointing to the total price,

00:42:40.029 --> 00:42:44.901
so, if someone focuses the amount,
also the total price is announced.

00:42:47.343 --> 00:42:49.022
and think about this,

00:42:49.046 --> 00:42:51.486
What will be the best
way for your use case?

00:42:51.511 --> 00:42:56.733
Is it the best way to add it to your
order button with an aria-label?

00:42:57.376 --> 00:43:02.349
Personally, I think in this
case you don't need ARIA at all.

00:43:02.769 --> 00:43:06.845
