00:48:37.490 --> 00:48:39.470
If you create something like this,

00:48:39.494 --> 00:48:43.186
you have to test it with all
kinds of different devices.

00:48:43.631 --> 00:48:44.917
User test.

00:48:46.420 --> 00:48:49.337
Because select2 doesn't
work for everyone,

00:48:50.547 --> 00:48:52.507
and you want people to contact you,

00:48:53.055 --> 00:48:55.954
order with you, subscribe
to your newsletter.

00:48:56.346 --> 00:48:58.525
Make that as easy as possible.

00:48:58.814 --> 00:49:01.354
Make that as predictable as possible.

00:49:03.275 --> 00:49:08.677
I want to quote Hayden Pickering:
"People don't want to be delighted.

00:49:09.026 --> 00:49:13.233
They want to do what they came
for, and then get on with their lives."

00:49:14.447 --> 00:49:17.683
That doesn't mean that
your form needs to be ugly.

00:49:18.040 --> 00:49:22.195
It can be pretty, and also usable
for as many people as possible,

00:49:22.802 --> 00:49:24.944
and that's the extra challenge.

00:49:25.381 --> 00:49:27.286
Discuss this with your designer.

00:49:30.830 --> 00:49:32.536
I'll end my ranting here.

00:49:32.561 --> 00:49:33.671
[chuckles]

00:49:34.560 --> 00:49:39.663
If you want to learn more about how to
create and code accessible web projects,

00:49:40.869 --> 00:49:45.658
I'd highly recommend you taking
a course at the a11y collective

00:49:45.683 --> 00:49:50.349
 at a11y-collective.com.

00:49:50.833 --> 00:49:55.259
My colleagues and I created courses
for everyone involved in the web project.

00:49:55.831 --> 00:49:59.607
Business owners,
stakeholders, project managers,

00:49:59.632 --> 00:50:04.249
content managers, designers,
and, of course, developers.

00:50:05.360 --> 00:50:08.764
The course about accessible
code will launch very soon,

00:50:09.529 --> 00:50:12.255
but to start there's also a basic course,

00:50:12.280 --> 00:50:16.143
where you can get a broad overview
of what accessibility actually is.

00:50:17.119 --> 00:50:20.671
If you're not sure, take
the free tryout course

00:50:20.703 --> 00:50:23.404
to get an impression of
what the courses are like.

00:50:23.908 --> 00:50:28.668
I hope you got an idea on how
ARIA can make a form understandable

00:50:29.239 --> 00:50:31.243
and give proper feedback.

00:50:32.704 --> 00:50:35.825
If you depend on a plugin for your forms,

00:50:35.849 --> 00:50:39.590
check if the plugin uses ARIA
to describe and give feedback.

00:50:40.297 --> 00:50:43.656
If labels are properly
connected to the form controls.

00:50:44.936 --> 00:50:46.723
Now you know
where to look out for.

00:50:48.308 --> 00:50:53.207
Research this before you implement
a plugin on your production website.

00:50:53.715 --> 00:50:57.707
You want everyone to be able to
understand your form, of course.

00:50:59.723 --> 00:51:02.091
Well, I hope I gave you a lot of homework,

00:51:03.341 --> 00:51:07.182
and I hope you got a better
understanding on how people use the web

00:51:07.531 --> 00:51:09.356
and your forms in a different way.

00:51:10.336 --> 00:51:11.557
Thank you for listening.

00:51:12.123 --> 00:51:13.677
Please be safe.

